    "notes": "High-fidelity indicators for T1543.003: (1) sc.exe spawned by a non-installer, non-SYSTEM process; (2) service ImagePath resolving to a user-writable path (AppData, Temp, ProgramData) rather than Program Files or System32; (3) services.exe launching a child process whose executable path is outside standard system directories. Correlate EID 1 (sc.exe create) + EID 13 (registry ImagePath write) + EID 1 (service binary launch from services.exe) within a short time window on the same host. False positive reduction: exclude binPath values matching C:\\Program Files\\* or C:\\Windows\\* when parent is msiexec.exe or a signed software updater."
